pylifemap

Overview

pylifemap is a jupyter widget allowing to visualize taxonomy data on Lifemap. It provides several visualisation layers, as well as aggregation functions allowing to aggregate data along the tree branches.

Here is a simple example:

import pandas as pd
from pylifemap import Lifemap

# Load iucn dataset
iucn = pd.read_csv(
    "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/juba/pylifemap/main/data/iucn.csv"
)

Lifemap(iucn).layer_points(radius=5, opacity=0.1).show()

Installation

For the moment the package can only be installed from Github:

pip install git+https://github.com/juba/pylifemap.git

You can also try the package without installing anything by using our introduction notebook in Google Colab:

Credits

  • The iucn data files in the data/ directory have been generated from The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species dataset (DOI 10.15468/0qnb58).
  • Visualizations are powered by Open Layers and deck.gl.
  • The widget is developed thanks to the anywidget framework.
